1.  Set up trust between
    {% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
    and
    {% $sca-project-variables.AWS-AD %}

    In this step you provide
    {% $sca-project-variables.AWS-AD %}
    with
    {% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
    details, and you provide
    {% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
    with
    {% $sca-project-variables.AWS-AD %}
    details:

    1.  Go to
        {% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %},
        \> [Apps & Widgets]{.Emphasis} \> [Web Apps]{.Emphasis} and
        select the web app that you created for the
        {% $sca-project-variables.AWS-AD %}.

    2.  Go to [Configure AWS for SSO:Â Step
        2](/identity/latest/en/content/applications/certified-apps/aws_saml_sso.htm#Step2SelecttheTrustpageintheIdentityAdministrationportaltoconfigureIdentityProviderandServiceProviderinformation)
        in the
        {% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
        docs and follow the instructions.

2.  If your organization uses
    {% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
    provisioning:

    1.  In
        {% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %},
        select the web app.

    2.  Under [Provisioning]{.Emphasis} go to the [Role
        Mappings]{.Emphasis} area.

    3.  Map the custom role you created above for the web app.

        For details about provisioning, see the [Provision accounts with
        SCIM](/identity/latest/en/content/applications/appsovw/scim-provisioning.htm "instructions on how to implement CyberArk Identity provisioning, including role mapping"){alt="instructions on how to implement CyberArk Identity provisioning, including role mapping"}
